DAY-SHIFT Report 2022-01-23, Sun
text: DAY-SHIFT Report 2022-01-23, Sun PROGRAM: User Beam, 500 mA, 300 s top-off injection BEAMLINES: All open FAULTS: 0835 BL7 BCS/PPS trips, causing PR1 fault, dumping SPEAR RF. Upon attending, determined that BL7-2 door keys in HPS chassis resulted in flickering contact made up for âHutch key in SRUâ circuit, despite being fully rotated into place. Was able to reproduce fault multiple times. Took BL7-2 offline, began relevant RSWCF and escalation procedures. SPEAR refilled and redelivered 500 mA beam with 300 s top-off injection by 0915 1630 BL10-2 LCW circuit #2 trips, causing PR2 fault, closing BL10. Adjusted flow, reset fault and BCS, and reopened beamline EXPERIMENTS: 0940 Filled RH 180 ltr dewar in LN fill station 0950 Filled Ge detector dewar on BL2-2 1015 Initiated RSWCF #2188 for BL7-2 HPS chassis repair 1030 Assisted experimenter on BL6-2 reporting inoperative vacuum pump on Lab 260 glove box. Pump had tripped off â restarted pump 1205 Placed gas order 1400 Assisted experimenter at BL2-1 reporting frozen software. Exited SPEC and restarted relevant systems per Ops Manual protocol (restart SPEC (twoc) load pilatus, camstart, pd enable). System restored 1530 Assisted experimenter at BL2-1 reporting non-functional shutter. Shutter was functional and controllable from SPEC commands âsopenâ and âsclose,â but not scan commands. Restarted SPEC, cam and pd functions without success. Discovered an automated shutter setting which was disabled but no deductive means to re-enable. Located last successful macro script with command âsautoâ which, with syntax âsauto 1â re-enabled shutter function when using count and scan commands. System restored
